Sun Oct 14 20:12:14 2001  George Lebl <jirka@5z.com>

	* libgnome/gnome-program.c: popt IS the evil incarnate.  There is no
	  reasonable way to pass data to the callbacks.  And we don't want
	  to modify or use the options.  So add a hack that sets
	  a data on the context with the GnomeProgram, so in a callback
	  if you want to get the GnomeProgram object you'd do
	  g_dataset_get_data (popt_context, "GnomeProgram");  Evil?
	  yes.  And it's the only way to do this sanely.

2001-10-10  Glynn Foster <glynn.foster@sun.com>

